{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9fb5c8b9-2dfb-4277-b733-a177d561e5f9","content":"**CLR activation logs won't help here.** They diagnose which .NET runtime version gets loaded (wrong runtime, missing runtime, FOD dialogs, etc.) — not application-level exceptions.\n\nA **NullReferenceException** is a runtime bug in your application code, not a CLR activation/loading issue.\n\n### What would actually help:\n\n1. **Stack trace** — share the full exception output (it will point to the exact line).\n2. **Application logs** — check stderr/stdout or any logging framework output.\n3. **Crash dump** — if you have one, I can help with analysis setup.\n4. **Source code** — share the startup/initialization code and I can review it.\n\nDo you have any of these available? That's the fastest path to finding the bug.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"23ec8195-69e8-4778-8419-78f51fb55f4b","outputTokens":180,"requestId":"2C43:1EA0BA:1457DF6:170E4EB:69F94B6E"},"id":"817f9a53-f76e-4a20-9d96-87d056f86e4b","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:44:20.635Z","parentId":"2226360b-f8ab-432c-acc8-fa1c133678fb"}
